<br>
My personal opinion is this:<br>
<br>
I don't mind folks who have ebayed or buy items for RL money.<br>
*shrug* If folks want to do this, it is fine by me. Frankly, I agree that most folks need to mind their own durned business and stop getting so hot in the collar about it. It smacks of envy and jealousy to me. If someone wants to spend their hard earned RL money on something, that's up to them. NOT ALL of us have wonderful artistic skills that we can use to profer in trade for plat like some people. I don't see a difference here. I can't draw worth diddly squat, but I can work in a Library in RL and make money doing that. I have abilities that lie elsewhere. If I could give something to that person in trade, I would. But if I want to use my money to buy items then I will do that too. IT IS MY DECISION. And No. I haven't done this yet, but frankly, I think folks are being a little inconsiderate here. I don't see anywhere where it says in the EULA that you can't exchange plat for RL money or goods or services rendered. I don't consider this cheating, because in my mind, making items in game or providing services there is a lot the same .. and we sell these things to get plat, so whats wrong with crossing the line to RL? *shrug* None in my book. If the person giving the plat away feels satisfied with the exchange, and the person getting the plat also does, no problem there that I see.<br>
<br>
The only thing I ever see in the EULa is about sharing or giving away accounts -- I don't agree with this practice, but again, Its none of my business unless some folk who doesn't know how to play the character they got gets me killed or acts like an ass. Then I just don't have to associate with them.<br>
