<br>
So let’s be honest and assert that most of the complaints here are because someone is offended. Now, we can justify that with EULA, morality, fair play, and etc. but in the end we are just trying to make ourselves feel better about something we cannot control. After all, what can you actually do? You could petition every toon that you believed was Ebayed, but nothing in our experience set shows that GMs or Sony really cares. You can flame Ebayed characters here, but if someone buys a toon they already either do not come to these boards or do not care about the repercussions here. <br>
<br>
The bottom line, however, is that it really does not affect you in any measurable way. Third level market effects or the inability to get into a raiding guild are just shadow arguments. The best thing is to open your mind and enjoy the game the way you want to and let others do the same. In the real world beating your head against a brick wall just hurts you no one else really cares. It works that way doubly so in EQ where the added veil of anonymous personas isolates us from real relationships.<br>
<br>
Open your mind. Ebay bigotry is no different from any other form of intolerance. It is borne out of own selfish desires to make everything and everyone conform to our view of right and wrong.<br>
<br>
